	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64667828">Replacing a microswitch is a trivial task for someone with soldering skills; if you know someone who has those skills, buy them a beer for replacing it; the switch itself isn't going to be proprietary, and it's manufacturer and part number will be printed on the case.<p>
But along the lines of your comment: microswitches could be mounted in socket pins, if they cared ro design the PCB that way, so that the end-user could easily replace them themselves.</p></div>
	</div>

